For added security and to enable extra caching, we are using self-hosted GitHub Action runners in a VPC so that the Open Cloud API can be restricted to our specific CIDR range. All-in-all, the game automatically publishes ~15 seconds after pushing any code or asset to GitHub!

Since the map is large, & all geometry, it is kept as a separate file, and we use Remodel to copy relevant code/assets into the map file (in S3) to produce a new release file. This allows for a dev file with minimal geometry & near instant load times during development process...

For the past few months since Rojo v7 alpha, Jailbreak has been fully managed, with all assets (except map) checked into version control. It has been an absolute dream for working on features in separate branches at the same time, and enables building off-machine... [2/4]

tech talk: #Jailbreak is now continuously deployed! When any new code or asset is pushed to develop branch on GitHub, an Action builds and publishes to QA testing place. I believe we are one of the first big games to take advantage of the new Open Cloud APIs in this manner! [1/4] https://t.co/OgW1rr72wo
